<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
    <meta name="description" content="EduConnect">
    <meta name="author" content="EduConnect">

    <title>EduConnect.com</title>

    <!-- Bootstrap core CSS -->
	  <%= stylesheet_link_tag    "static_pages"%>
	  <%= stylesheet_link_tag    "bootstrap", :media => "all" %>

    <!-- Latest compiled and minified CSS -->

<%= javascript_include_tag  "ie-emulation-modes-warning" %>
<%= javascript_include_tag  "ie10-viewport-bug-workaround" %>



    <!-- Custom styles for this template -->
  </head>
<!-- NAVBAR
================================================== -->
  <body>

    <div id="myCarousel" class="carousel slide" data-ride="carousel">
      <!-- Indicators -->
      <ol class="carousel-indicators">
        <li data-target="#myCarousel" data-slide-to="0" class="active"></li>
        <li data-target="#myCarousel" data-slide-to="1"></li>
        <li data-target="#myCarousel" data-slide-to="2"></li>
      </ol>
      <div class="carousel-inner">
        <div class="item active">
          <img src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAHd3dwAAACH5BAAAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAICRAEAOw==" alt="First slide">
          <div class="container">
            <div class="carousel-caption">
              <h1>Example headline.</h1>
              <p>Note: If you're viewing this page via a <code>file://</code> URL, the "next" and "previous" Glyphicon buttons on the left and right might not load/display properly due to web browser security rules.</p>
              <p><a class="btn btn-lg btn-primary" href="#" role="button">Sign up today</a></p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="item">
          <img src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAGZmZgAAACH5BAAAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAICRAEAOw==" alt="Second slide">
          <div class="container">
            <div class="carousel-caption">
              <h1>Another example headline.</h1>
              <p>Cras justo odio, dapibus ac facilisis in, egestas eget quam. Donec id elit non mi porta gravida at eget metus. Nullam id dolor id nibh ultricies vehicula ut id elit.</p>
              <p><a class="btn btn-lg btn-primary" href="#" role="button">Learn more</a></p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="item">
          <img src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAFVVVQAAACH5BAAAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAICRAEAOw==" alt="Third slide">
          <div class="container">
            <div class="carousel-caption">
              <h1>One more for good measure.</h1>
              <p>Cras justo odio, dapibus ac facilisis in, egestas eget quam. Donec id elit non mi porta gravida at eget metus. Nullam id dolor id nibh ultricies vehicula ut id elit.</p>
              <p><a class="btn btn-lg btn-primary" href="#" role="button">Browse gallery</a></p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <a class="left carousel-control" href="#myCarousel" role="button" data-slide="prev"> <span class= "glyphicon glyphicon-chevron-left"> </span></a>
      <a class="right carousel-control" href="#myCarousel" role="button" data-slide="next"> <span class= "glyphicon glyphicon-chevron-right"> </span></a>
    </div><!-- /.carousel -->



    <!-- Marketing messaging and featurettes
    ================================================== -->
    <!-- Wrap the rest of the page in another container to center all the content. -->

    <div class="container marketing">

      <!-- Three columns of text below the carousel -->
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-lg-4">
                  <%= image_tag "alumni.jpg", :class=>"img-circle", :alt => "Generic placeholder image",:height => "140px", :width => "140px" %>
          <h2>Alumni</h2>
          <p>Get a chance to check out alumni profiles to view what projects they achieved while studying and in which industries plus departments they are working in after graduation</p>
          <p><%= link_to "View All &raquo;".html_safe, '/alumnis', :class =>"btn btn-default" , :role=>"button" %></p>
        </div><!-- /.col-lg-4 -->
        <div class="col-lg-4">
                  <%= image_tag "campus.jpg", :class=>"img-circle", :alt => "Generic placeholder image",:height => "140px", :width => "140px" %>

		<h2>University</h2>
          <p> Check out the profiles of all the universities registered in order to check what majors they offer, yearly tuition costs, and a variety of projects created by alumnis from various majors </p>
          <p>   <%= link_to "View All &raquo;".html_safe, '/universities', :class =>"btn btn-default" , :role=>"button" %></p>
        </div><!-- /.col-lg-4 -->
        <div class="col-lg-4">
                  <%= image_tag "diploma.jpg", :class=>"img-circle", :alt => "Generic placeholder image",:height => "140px", :width => "140px" %>
          <h2>Majors</h2>
          <p>Browse into what majors are offered worldwide with a description of what each major is, which universities are offering this major and where are graduates working</p>
          <p><%= link_to "View All &raquo;".html_safe, '/majors', :class =>"btn btn-default" , :role=>"button" %></p>
        </div><!-- /.col-lg-4 -->
      </div><!-- /.row -->


      <!-- START THE FEATURETTES -->

      <hr class="featurette-divider">

      <div class="row featurette">
        <div class="col-md-7">
          <h2 class="featurette-heading">Carnegie Mellon University <span class="text-muted">Pittsburgh Campus</span></h2>
          <p class="lead">For more than a century, Carnegie Mellon University has been inspiring innovations that change the world. Consistently top ranked, Carnegie Mellon has more than 12,000 students, 95,000 alumni and 5,000 faculty and staff globally</p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-5">
          <%= image_tag "cmuq.jpg", :alt => "slide1",:height => "300px", :width => "380px", :style => " border: 0px solid " %>
        </div>
      </div>

      <hr class="featurette-divider">

      <div class="row featurette">
        <div class="col-md-5">
          <%= image_tag "nuq.jpg", :alt => "slide1",:height => "300px", :width => "410px", :style => " border: 0px solid " %>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-7">
          <h2 class="featurette-heading">NorthWestern University <span class="text-muted">Qatar Campus</span></h2>
          <p class="lead">NU-Q is not just a media school, however; it's a community of students who undertake a broad and rigorous curriculum in the liberal arts that enriches their capacity for critical thinking and broadens their world-view. The university ensures that graduates are broadly educated in areas beyond their specialties with an emphasis on cultivating flexibility of mind and a capacity for critical thinking and clear expression.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <hr class="featurette-divider">

      <div class="row featurette">
        <div class="col-md-7">
          <h2 class="featurette-heading">Texas A&M University <span class="text-muted">Qatar Campus</span></h2>
          <p class="lead"> Since the fall of 2003, Texas A&M University at Qatar has offered Bachelor of Science degrees in chemical engineering, electrical engineering, mechanical engineering and petroleum engineering. In addition to engineering courses, Texas A&M University at Qatar provides instruction in science, mathematics, liberal arts and the humanities. The curriculum offered at Texas A&M at Qatar are identical to the ones offered at the main campus in College Station, Texas.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-5">
          <%= image_tag "tamuq.jpg", :alt => "slide1",:height => "350px", :width => "450px", :style => " border: 0px solid " %>
        </div>
      </div>


      <!-- /END THE FEATURETTES -->


      <!-- FOOTER -->
   
    </div><!-- /.container -->


    <!-- Bootstrap core JavaScript
    ================================================== -->
    <!-- Placed at the end of the document so the pages load faster -->
    <%= javascript_include_tag  "docs.min","bootstrap.min", "jquery.min" %>
    
  </body>
</html>
